
[1]tasting

   TASTING, ppr. Perceiving by the tongue.

   1. Trying; experiencing; enjoying or suffering.

              TASTING, n. The art of perceiving by the tongue.

   1. The sense by which we perceive of distinguish savors; or the
   perception of external objects through the instrumentality of the
   tongue or organs of taste.
